title: Clean Bandit - Rather Be (feat. Jess Glynne) (Official Video) 72
description:
"Rather Be" is a song by British electronic group Clean Bandit, featuring vocals from Jess Glynne. The track was released on 17 January 2014 as the fourth single from the group's debut studio album, New Eyes (2014).[1][2] Musically, 'Rather Be' is a deep house and synthpop song that lyrically portrays the protagonists infatuation with her significant other; stating she doesn't want to be anywere else.
The song debuted at number one on the UK Singles Chart, and is the fastest-selling single of 2014 so far, and the highest selling January single since "Spaceman" by Babylon Zoo, which reached number one in 1996.[3] The song has spent four weeks at number one, selling over 1,000,000 copies since release.[
